## Post 2
- Link: https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7446981364840681472/
- Type: Text
- Summary:
  Amanda shares that marketing partnerships can fail not because they are overpriced, but because they are under-scoped. What appears as a simple deliverable can evolve into complex, iterative work involving multiple approvals, feedback loops, and constraints.
- Key Insight:
  In scalable marketing systems, clarity of scope and process is critical. As AI accelerates content production, the bottleneck shifts to coordination, feedback, and execution complexity—making structured workflows and clear boundaries essential for maintaining efficiency and ROI.
